Description: TSEW RAID Web Appliance Manager
 Secure, lightweight storage management appliance implementing TRAID
 (TSEW RAID). Uses a split-privilege architecture: an unprivileged
 FastAPI/Uvicorn web interface communicates over a Unix socket with a
 privileged worker daemon that executes mdadm, lvm, and parted to
 manage mismatched drives using a tier-slicing algorithm.
